<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-21T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-21T18:00:00-05:00" n="221" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1854</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Page</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-21T23:00:00+00:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1917, 11 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>8038. Your 5876 November 22, 5 p.m. Currency loan to China. Foreign
                            Office informs me to-day matter has been referred to Treasury and have
                            promised that the decision, as soon as it is reached, will be
                            communicated to me.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>